But not only did North West premier Supra Mahumapelo use the F-word against DA chief whip John Steenhuisen, he failed to own up to it for almost a week. When it was clear he would be caught, he wrote an "apology letter" that amounted to a middle finger to the public, blaming his foul mouth on an "off-the-record altercation" with Steenhuisen. This from a man who mentions God in every conversation.